Like Enviroman said just email or ask in the comments section of the
blog so that the blog owner will get the message.

There is also a thing known as a &quot;blogroll&quot; where a link to your blog
is added that way.  Someone could happen upon your blog, like your
content and add you to their blogroll.

Basically the rules of copyright infringement say that you cannot put
copyrighted material -and that includes images - if you don't have
permission from the copyrighted owner.  Now of course people still do
this kind of thing but even so its better to be safe then sorry!  You
could always email the copyright owner and ask their permission.

Perez Hilton has a very popular celebrity gossip blog but he's been
having trouble because he posts celebrity pictures of which  it is
disputed whether or not he has the right to add them to his blog.

So I repeat - It's better to be safe than sorry!
